SIMPLE: tope
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tope
<hw>Tope</hw> <pr>(t⟦omac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably from
Skr. <ets>st⟦umac⟧pa</ets> a tope, a stupa, through Prakrit
<ets>th⟦umac⟧po</ets>.]</ety> <def>A moundlike Buddhist sepulcher, or
memorial monument, often erected over a Buddhist relic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tope
<hw>Tope</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Tamil <ets>t⟦omac⟧ppu</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A grove or clump of trees; <as>as, a toddy
<ex>tope</ex></as>.</def> <mark>[India]</mark>
<rj><au>Whitworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Tope
<hw>Tope</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
shark or dogfish (<spn>Galeorhinus galeus</spn> syn. <spn>Galeus
galeus</spn>), native of <geog>Europe</geog>, but found also on the
coasts of <state>California</state> and <geog>Tasmania</geog>; -- called
also <altname>toper</altname>, <altname>oil shark</altname>,
<altname>miller's dog</altname>, and <altname>penny
dog</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The wren.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tope</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Tope
<hw>Tope</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Toped</conjf> <pr>(t⟦omac⟧pt)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Toping</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>t⟦ocir⟧per</ets> to cover
a stake in playing at dice, to accept an offer, <ets>t⟦ocir⟧pe</ets>
agreed!; -- perhaps imitative of the sound of striking hands on
concluding a bargain. From being used in English as a drinking term,
probably at first in accepting a toast.]</ety> <def>To drink hard or
frequently; to drink strong or spiritous liquors to excess.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If you <qex>tope</qex> in form, and treat.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Topek</ent>⟦br⟧
